A> at: 12/13/01 8:27:47 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ujsmiff69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jsmiff69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CAMEL TOES!!!</span><br>  Posts: 1148<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/13/01 8:35:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.rit.edu/~jgs1536/media/dancingstewie3.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anti Summoning Shield</span><hr size=1> Mages hate verant, plain and simple...<br>it stems first from our not getting roots/snares so that if we get aggro without a pet up, we either run, gate, or die.<br><br>next... in lower levels, we can nuke about on par with a wizard... later on, the wizard greatly out damages us... near the end, druids are now on par with us nuke-wise...  so while we had a good start, we're now second-class nukers...<br><br>next... pathing is a joke in most raid zones... and despite walls allowing casters to shield from AE's, the game mechanics still recognizes that the AE SHOULD hit through the wall, so despite the casters NOT getting hit, the pets still register it as aggro and run around the wall to go defend their master... read - pets unusable in some high-end encounters due to this.<br><br>next... coh... ahh, we love to hate it.  It makes us useful for raids... it used to give us a quick way to drop aggro and camp out to help with CR's.  However, thanks to all the people taking advantage of the aggro-removal, CoH was initially completely nerfed, fixed, and then only partially nerfed.  With the release of Luclin, we now find one of our only class-defining abilities and our most useful raid-spell useless - either not working at all or summoning KoS 32khp mobs.<br><br>Back to nuking, but for high end... until resistances were lowered, magicians could not nuke a single high-end mob... not until Tash/malo/malosini/occlusion were all in... even then it was iffy.  So we got demoted to mod rod whores who could MAYBE use their pets if the situation permitted.<br><br>FINALLY... you have the mage epic.  Otherwise known as Verant giving the mage community as a whole the finger.  Other epics have bottlenecks, I'm not saying they don't.  But the mage epic far and away is horrible.  Rare drops off ultra-rare spawns that are also sought after by everyone (quillmane), in horrible time sink zones (PoA crown off 7th isle), or just plain sadistic games of chance (hate staff/burning embers/power of fire)<br><br>Now, they completely remove a spell that had lots of possibilities, instead of just removing the unbalancing portion of it, and you wonder why mages are pissed off?  We have a LOT of built up resentment, heh. <p><center><h4>Bacris Spellbinder</h4><h5>59 Conjurer<br>The Companions</h5><br><Br><img src = http://www.rit.edu/~jgs1536/media/makino.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uclavonixdemandred.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Clavonix Demandred</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/13/01 3:02:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anti Summoning Shield</span><hr size=1> You guys have a lot of good points, makes me mad thinking about all the time i've put into being a mage but I'm too stubborn to ever quit.  What I think you should all do though is start putting these arguments of yours on the shittiness of VI's nerfing in the form of /feedback.  Call me idealistic, but maybe if we /feedback every single day for 6 months VI will have t